    "body": "@micieslak another point, I don't think this is UI logic we move to the backend. It's the opposite. This is all logic that **should have** been in the backend from the start, because it's data fetching. It wasn't done like that because we were noob (aka me, I did that code lol) and because the setting to show the links was only QML side before.\r\n\r\n@alexjba when/if you work on this, remember to check the setting to show links first before fetching data.\r\nThis is very important. Some people do specifically do not want to show the links so they don't show their IP address to sites.\r\n\r\nAlso, make sure to the use the thread tasks that already exist. Querying from some sites was already slow, so if we wait on the backend fetch before showing anything, it's gonna create a very bad UX. So if possible, when creating the message, we just show the link with no data, then we populate the link data when we finish fetching it with events and signals.",
